      "text": [
        " مَنْ شَرِبَ الْخَمْرَ لَمْ يَقْبَلِ اللَّهُ لَهُ صَلَاةً أَرْبَعِينَ يَوْماً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Abdul Rahman Bin Al Hajjaj, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who drinks the wine, his Prayer would not be Accepted from him for forty days’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from ‘Abd al-Rahman ibn al-Hajj aj who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘If one drinks wine his Salat (prayer) is not accepted for forty days.’” "
        ]
      }
